<p>Sentences Act is horribly difficult &ndash; unless you go by the rule of thumb method which is in favour in English Army.</p>
<p>Has Dick Windeyer got his silk yet? He must be a very disappointed man if he has not, and I hope the Bar Council is not setting up my wishes as an excuse for objecting.</p>
<p>Well this letter is getting beyond bounds and I am a weary of this great world, the day's work having included a lecture to a distant S/Majors's school,  on discipline &ndash; illustrated by several new and humorous anecdotes. There has also been some bike pushing through cold winds. The leaves are falling and summer is gone.<br/>Goodbye<br/>Em Brissenden</p>
